<h1> Dish 1: Spam Musubi </h1>

<b> Recipe 1, Provided by Ms. Tama Abe </b>

<p>Ingredients:</p>

1 Can of Spam<br/>
3 Cups Uncooked Sushi Rice<br/>
Sugar<br/>
Soy Sauce<br/>
Nori Sheets<br/>
Furikake or Li Hing Mui<br/>
A musubi-maker<br/>
<br/>

<p>Directions:</p>

1.	Make sure to have all of your ingredients ready to go so the Spam stays crisp<br/>
2.	Remember that this is all up to you and your preference; don’t measure anything precisely! Generally, we use three cups of rice per one can of Spam.<br/>
3.	Slice the block of Spam into eight pieces.<br/>
4.	Mix equal amounts of soy sauce and sugar into a bowl.<br/>
5.	Put the sliced Spam in a sauté pan and fry.<br/>
6.	Wait a few minutes and put the soy sauce and sugar on top of the Spam. Once the Spam is crispy enough, transfer the mixture to a plate.<br/>
7.	Moving quickly – cut the nori strips in half lengthwise and put the musubi-maker on the middle of the nori. Scoop some rice into the mold. Press the rice down well.<br/>
8.	Add a thin layer of furikake on top of the rice. Add one slice of Spam and then garnish with more furikake. Add some more rice, and press it down again.<br/>
9.	Last, wrap the nori around the rice, and serve!<br/>
